commit_message:
Merge pull request #2 from jackwadden/remove_subprocess

Remove subprocess
Major updates to improve speed and add online mode. This version of LAMPrey was used for all online end-to-end runs for the final paper submission.
Added prototype online monitoring code that takes a fast5 directory where squiggles are dumped, copies them locally, basecalls them, and then processes them.
Adding prototype watchdog functionality for true real-time analysis.
Slight modifications to high_confidence mode (renamed to confidence_level) to allow for parameterized concatemer filtering for VAF computation.
Fixed bug where searching left would break if the final correct primer sequence was identified but was not the last primer.
Fixed issue where I wasn't revcomping reverse target sub-reads before alignment.
First prototype completely removing subprocess calls. Led to a ~10x speedup.
Still mucking around. Biopython is just a wrapper for subprocess, so that was a dead end.
First working candidate with removal of minimap2 dependency.
First ripout of subprocess.
Merge branch 'swaccel' of https://github.com/jackwadden/lamprey into swaccel
Checkpoint of skbio integration.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jackwadden/lamprey into swaccel
misc updates to high confidence mode
Swapped swalign for scikit-bio sw aligner. Huge speed improvements, but small change to results.
Shrunk example dataset and updated quick start usage.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jackwadden/lamprey
Removing .gitignore
Fixed missing script issue and also a relative path in process_candidates.sh
Updating README.md
Adding progressbar to requrements.
Fixed wrong link to run script.
Removed .gitignore
Updated README to be more specific and added cython to requirements.txt
Adding proper paths to example run scripts.
Adding lib directory path.

Merge pull request #1 from jackwadden/add-license-1

Create LICENSE
Create LICENSE
Updating README.
Updating README.
Updated instructions for downloading and installing lamprey and accelerated swalign.
Updating README.
Adding scripts and data for example use.
Updates to classification algorithm to fix issues with off target classifications.
Major refactor to improve readability and organization of lamplicon processing algorithm.
Factored out lamplicon polishing into own function.
Modified code to include and emit plural base classifications over the target to augment existing majority VAF voting.
Added prototype lamplicon polishing functionality.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jackwadden/lamprey
Made timestamp parsing and sorting an option in case bonito is used as a basecaller. Also allowed for fasta input.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jackwadden/lamprey
Moved num threads var to cl option.
Added consensus polishing results and reporting from aligned target sub-reads.
Updated requirements.
Added in progream header and prototype summary result output.
First prototype of multiprocess implementation. Major update to parallelize workload and clean up output generation and add simple progressbar to output.
Added time parsing and modified confidence interval printing code. Allows for identification of statistical significance over hardcoded background error rate.

Identified subprocess calls as source of slowdown. Refactored sub-concatemer alignment and pileup into single script (process_candidates.sh) and make a single call. Also removed consensus calling script and capability for now. Will add back in eventually.
Fixed minor bug when in high confidence mode.
Added --high_confidence option to filter out any lamplicon Mut/Wt calls <2 depth.
Added profiling skeleton code.
Minor output formatting changes and fixes.
Updating to newest dev code

Major updates that remove any primer/target specific code. Lamprey now takes a VCF file as input that identifies the target within the target fasta input (not the subject genome). Colorized pretty printing (with some remaining bugs). Aggregate/disaggregate VAF computation. Next commit will clean up code and work on acceleration.
Adding script to perform pileup
some bug fixes and sloppy experimental changes. Will clean up code and re-write the core now.

Continued code cleanup

 - use library for arg parsing, removed commented code, printing optional

Added basic script for plotting raw signals

 - lamplicons not easily cut based on raw signal information

Read through code to understand, cleaned up, few minor fixes

 - BUGFIX: findPrimerAlignments now uses local, not global
 - 'name' -> 'primer_name' for clarity
 - better defaults for accuracy calculation
 - misc changes to make code more clean/readable

Added project build instructions

 - project assumes python3.6, package management with virtualenv
 - Git now ignores output SAM/BAM files
Git now ignores data/ and run.sh
Fixed a few bugs wrt extending amplicons around a target.
Added functionality that removes leading and trailing ambiguous consensus characters.
Added alignment, consensus, and manipulation scripts to scripts/ dir
Added error rate calculator script and updated README.
Updating README and adding support scripts for sam_to_bam conversion and error rate calculation.
Updating README with basic usage.
Added usage and removed raw paths to files.
Working prototype. Added a fudge factor to account for primers that don't quite align. Fudge factor causes a small error where reads end up with a final mismatched primer attached.
Added fasta output of combined/parsed targets
Adding prototype lamp region/target aligner.
first commit
